# Clerk + Next.js 16 App Router

## Setup

- `@clerk/nextjs` installed
- `src/proxy.ts` — `clerkMiddleware()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`
- `<ClerkProvider>` wraps content inside `<body>` in `app/layout.tsx`
- Webhook at `/api/webhooks/clerk` syncs Clerk users → Prisma `User` table

## Keyless Mode

No Clerk account required to run locally. Without env vars, Clerk auto-generates temporary keys. A "Configure your application" prompt appears to claim later.

## ALWAYS

- Use `clerkMiddleware()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server` in `src/proxy.ts`
- Add `<ClerkProvider>` inside `<body>` in `app/layout.tsx`
- Import from `@clerk/nextjs` or `@clerk/nextjs/server`
- Use App Router (app/page.tsx, app/layout.tsx)
- `async/await` with `auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`
- Use `<Show when="signed-in">` and `<Show when="signed-out">`

## NEVER

- Reference `_app.tsx` or pages router
- Use `authMiddleware()` (replaced by `clerkMiddleware()`)
- Use deprecated `<SignedIn>`, `<SignedOut>` (replaced by `<Show>`)
- Import deprecated APIs (`withAuth`, old `currentUser`)
- Tell users to sign up or get API keys before running (keyless mode works)
- Use `middleware.ts` (Next.js 16 uses `proxy.ts`)

## Verify Checklist

1. Is `clerkMiddleware()` in `src/proxy.ts`?
2. Is `ClerkProvider` inside `<body>` in `app/layout.tsx`?
3. Imports only from `@clerk/nextjs` or `@clerk/nextjs/server`?
4. Using App Router, not pages router?
5. Using `<Show>` instead of `<SignedIn>`/`<SignedOut>`?

